begin_memory_text: The study, what it might be about, past experiences with people showing up/not showing up. That we both got the notice only an hour ago. Then where are yous?
middle_memory_text: Climate change, fires, fires in the west, GA, then experiences with natural disasters and what we expect where we live.
end_memory_text: More about climate change and then into a mutual introverts judgey mutual rant about the pandemic and how people act/do not act and how we were doing well compared to others who we empathized with, but did not understand. Then he segued into us ending on TIME! I know you are happy about that :) I was.
rest_of_day_open: I don't know? I was really tired today and hope that I have mote energy and get lots of things done this week. I did vote today, so that was a big deal done. That makes the whole week successful if it is all I do. In a perfect world I would mow my grass and stain my deck too.
critical_positive: It went pretty well for a man and a woman who are strangers and a little closer in age. Not very close, but he did not take over the whole thing and he seemed less relaxed than most of the woman have been, but he loosened up. I think we agreed on a lot and that helped.
critical_negative: There was some awkwardness as I tried to not interrupt and be a better listener. IT was awkward for him too since I told him I was doing it. So we both worked around me trying to change my impulse to interrupt. It didn't always go as effortless as I would have liked.

begin_memory_text: We talked about the purpose of this study and how we have both had numerous conversations as part of the previous series and the current series.
middle_memory_text: We talked about states we lived in and specifically the weather types that could affect them, especially disastrous weather and how those could really be unpredictable.
end_memory_text: We talked largely about the pandemic as we were talking about how people have short-lived memories in terms of forgetting the lessons they've learned for the pandemic and wanting to live lives the way they did back when times were normal.
rest_of_day_open: I think I am going to have some really stressful times at work.  At home I'll largely be continuing to play a video game and hopefully get another chat or two in.  I've been oversleeping lately so I suspect that will continue to be an issue for me in terms of exhaustion seeping into aspects of my life.
critical_positive: My conversation partner was really willing to talk.  This made it pretty easy for me to keep the conversation going despite the fact I am by no stretch of the imagination someone who usually does pretty well with communication.  She was easily able to continue the conversation by bringing up whatever personal/academic examples.
critical_negative: Although it mostly went well, the things I struggled with were my partner was generally hard to find an opening with in the conversation and her webcam was not angled well, so I couldn't see her well to be able to read her gestures much.  I saw a smile here or there or a chuckle so I wasn't totally in the dark, but that made it hard to know what reactions there were.
